Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a drab-coloured pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the exterior is covered with a red-brown slip and remains of five lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393795) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393795)
